multilevel regression(Chinese data)

Jiaxin Li

2024-03-29

Conclusion:

The following analysis of the data from China shows that there is no significant difference in the feedback values given by participants for 3 outcome variables across different “feed_type” groups. And the “Durationinseconds” variable also doesn’t have significant effect on 3 outcome variables across different “feed_type” groups.

1. packages and libraries

2. upload the chinese data

chinese_data_filtered <- read.csv("CNdata_filtered_120123.csv")
chinese_data_filtered$feed_type <- factor(chinese_data_filtered$feed_type)

chinese_data_filtered$feed_type <- ifelse(chinese_data_filtered$valence == 2,
                                          paste0("neg_", chinese_data_filtered$feed_type),
                                          paste0("pos_", chinese_data_filtered$feed_type))

chinese_data_filtered$feed_type <- factor(chinese_data_filtered$feed_type)

unique(chinese_data_filtered$feed_type)
## [1] neg_ad    pos_memes pos_news  neg_memes neg_act   pos_ad    neg_news 
## [8] pos_act  
## 8 Levels: neg_act neg_ad neg_memes neg_news pos_act pos_ad ... pos_news

3. multilevel model for “credibility”:

The analysis of the data from China shows that there is no significant difference in the feedback values given by participants for the variable “credibility” across different “feed_type” groups.

3.1 partial pooling (feed_type)

partial pooling (feed_type) brings mean of the credibility of 8 different feed type groups.

#install.packages("lme4")
library(lme4)
md_chinese_cred_fit1 <- lmer(credavg_all ~ 1 + (1 | feed_type), data=chinese_data_filtered)
# partial pooling brings the within group mean 
# to the across group mean
summary(md_chinese_cred_fit1)
## Linear mixed model fit by REML ['lmerMod']
## Formula: credavg_all ~ 1 + (1 | feed_type)
##    Data: chinese_data_filtered
## 
## REML criterion at convergence: 1153.8
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -3.3665 -0.5809  0.1101  0.7423  1.7918 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups    Name        Variance Std.Dev.
##  feed_type (Intercept) 0.006458 0.08036 
##  Residual              0.625658 0.79099 
## Number of obs: 484, groups:  feed_type, 8
## 
## Fixed effects:
##             Estimate Std. Error t value
## (Intercept)  3.64944    0.04589   79.53
print(coef(md_chinese_cred_fit1)[[1]])
##           (Intercept)
## neg_act      3.630024
## neg_ad       3.630533

## pos_news     3.662887

3.4 visualizations

ggplot(chinese_data_filtered)+
  geom_point(aes(x=Durationinseconds, y=credavg_all, color = feed_type))+
  geom_smooth(aes(x=Durationinseconds, y=credavg_all, color = feed_type), formula = "y~x", method="lm", se=F)+
  facet_wrap(~feed_type)+
  theme(legend.position = "none")+
  scale_color_viridis(discrete = T, option = "B")+
  labs(title = "Complete Pooling", xlab="Durationinseconds", ylab="Credibility")
